content: Today we will study another game from World Championship final.
it is my game with Vladimir Sushkov
I was black and he was white.
As you know, I lost that game.
It started here, I put d3, he kept whites,
Then I decided to try the style that I had not played in my previous games.
I used the three to k10.
There are two possible styles from here:
one is k7, another is h10.
Since h10 is not so often played,
so I decided to use it.
All these 15 moves are natural development in this variant.
I have seen several 16th moves here.
this funny 16th move is a provocation.
Black seems to have no vct here..
then maybe balancing style looks nice.
and black is not bad after all.
maybe here the black is too active.
and can use too much of the space
but with 16-g6, the space is not so good for black
taking the risk of being surrounded if I dont win
after 17 white can do anything,no pressure
Of course, white is so good on left side
but I was hoping to increase the pressure,
with the help of i6 support
it is more risky for black
just pick up one of them...
all seems thst black will be in trouble..
black wants to win so much... but where!
but Sushkov didnt use that 24 at all
m9 so near to this m10...
and it closes the connection to i6
this 24 is a double win point for black
but there is chance for under
I was preparing the lower side space
He thought about the defense here,
maybe n9, maybe L7, maybe j5,
what did he choose, do you know?
Interesting is that later Tunnet and Stefan chose the same block - middle.
As you know, I tested this variant 3 times,
with Sushkov, I thought about the longer perspective..
My idea was to play here..
cut the white connection in upper right.
You see, I was planning the attack below..
and i thought, the m9 four will be useful support for black
so I thought, if I could block the 10_24 early,
then later the black four at m9 supports better
it is better for your attacking
what if he had played like this
whats the next plan for black?
anyway, he was a bit worried about black's attack on the left,
thats why he played 30th move in the middle, as I had counted for.
in any other case, white would take that point
And now I was thinking of some space development
but this block at i6 bothered me a lot
it's now the key develop move
I think this point was important for me,
And now, I spent some time to seek for the good spot in lower area.
I wanted to play like k5...
but I worried about the counter-attack from f7..
is this move white's VCF threat?
lets wait until everyone sees it
say yes when you see it
if you cannot see many steps with calculation
but we shouldnt use ity as possible as we could
who wants to show the win, say me
sometime is easy to see VCF, but hard to see the cut :)
So I would have to block here maybe..

claire, leto, luwenzhe, Southerner, iris, shuwang, Ikon, smiling, weigui, Chancewu, coco_yuang, pantrike, yyfcsd, smallpig, whte, Alan, jamphen, xiebin123xie, shaoping, nick_hopper, eastmen, concord2497, moocheng, span, killer21st, LiuJianping, pengyu.
which is maybe not bad, considering that black will have two areas for the attack
the upper area is not maybe so good for black anymore
so in the game with Stefan later,
I didnt not use 29-k12, for this reason.
not giving him the chance for the active game.
if this time white goes up there
so, he could not play any active 36th move,
He took away the strong point.
Now, I could finally develop into space, without worries.
but I didn't like this stone at i5 of course.

don't do that leto !!! next time you win okay
and later I regretted that I didnt play the three out to g4.
So in my game with Tunnet, I already used g4 three first.
Now I was very close to win, I thought.
He had quite short time left.
who wants to show, say ME
where does white have to block?
but Sushkov was so mean, he didnt choose this 40th move
even though he had like 2minutes left or so
you did the good job ..fancy style
but he found the correct move again
had he played elsewhere, then the lower side would have become very strong
now black cannot win because of the cut!
but too bad, the line 50_46_40 ruined the plan
So, I spent lots of my time here,
so I had to give up the idea of winning here,
the class is just for this purpose - to be active and try out
I hope there are more students who are willin to rise up the question and try out
because this is study, not tournament
I tried to drag out the remains of my force towards left wing

leto, claire, Southerner, luwenzhe, pantrike, killer21st, Ikon, Chancewu, shaoping, coco_yuang, jamphen, whte, iris, weigui, moocheng, nick_hopper, pengyu, LiuJianping, concord2497, shuwang, Intotherenju, span, yyfcsd, xiebin123xie, smiling, smallpig, eastmen.
although it was not hard to block the lower side, I was more worried about the upper side..
he had quite little time left..
and my time was like 2 minutes left
It takes some tactics to fill up the board,
It was hard task to do in time-trouble
Claire was beside the game table
I thought it looks well here..
I have many pitctures that many ppl around the table watching the game .. that gave more pressure
I thought I can go on from here..
wow,put them on the forum.lets share them
sure sure i will arrange them later
I realized, I cannot leave this corner with the tempo
and I cannot use the three either
but now white could put the stone to upper side first.
both players clocks were running out soon
hoping to create further confusion in lower part
when he will have his last 10-20 seconds
he had 30 seconds left, I had 50 seconds...
white is in advantage in blitz
this is where you cannot calculate very much,
but need to use the intuition and feeling.
then stopped my hand in half way
both of their face are so red ... also ears
and you know, right after the game
I said i wanted to play d9...
and he said, he was going to play next move toh14
but then I could have won
so it was like big lotter of time trouble
it could have been either one's win in last seconds, it should have been draw..
when the game ended, he had about 20 seconds on the clock, I had 30 seconds
so,Ando RT,you should believe your first feeling:)
there was no time to think about it.
claire, this is on video, too, right?
and no time to feel too
it was a tough game, indeed.
ha  am i saw the cam b4 ???
you did a good job .. but Sushkov is well prepared this time ..
the last moves were like a lottery game
he would have lost by time maybe,
as I saw .. he is very calm .. in every game ...
I hope there is the video recording about it, I will check later.
Claire did a very very good job during the tournament, lots of videos and photos.
and we will publish them later here,
I wonder if the server has enough space ? Lu ?
I am glad to hear it.
it must be a big file
during the WC, I was not able to prove the effectiveness of this variant,
I got 1 lss and 2 draws from this variant
but I can photoshop a lil bit make them smaller
Conclusion: dont put yourself in time trouble
but with aothers 9th move black is not good too
so, the variant was not well chosen.
I was close to win many times,
we can all admire his skill.
ando tried to play something different out of theory .. or challenge some new moves
Claire pointed out very important thing indeed.
a lion encountered is very dangerous, is a Go proverbe...
All my games were like search for something new.
I did not want to repeat any known things.
like a shuskov in time trouble...
This was a good tactics for art, but not good tactics for sport.
almost every game I asked ando .. "are you going to try out new moves or just play safely and win ?"  .... but ando chose to try ...
we will end the lesson now
